        <section>
            <title>Articles</title>

            <para>If you would like to know more about the internal workings of eXist, you may read
                the following introductory article:</para>

            <para>Wolfgang Meier. <ulink url="xmlprague06.xml">Index-Driven XQuery Processing in the
                    eXist XML Database</ulink>. Paper presented at XML Prague 2006. Presentation
                slides can be found <ulink
                    href="http://wiki.exist-db.org/space/XMLPrague2006/wolfgangs_talk.pdf"
                >here</ulink> as well.</para>

            <para>An older article is:</para>
            
            <para>Wolfgang Meier. <ulink url="http://exist-db.org/webdb.pdf">eXist: An Open Source
                    Native XML Database</ulink>. In: Akmal B. Chaudri, Mario Jeckle, Erhard Rahm,
                Rainer Unland (Eds.): Web, Web-Services, and Database Systems. NODe 2002 Web- and
                Database-Related Workshops, Erfurt, Germany, October 2002. Springer LNCS Series,
                2593.</para>

            <para>A chapter about eXist is also contained in the book:</para>

            <para>Akmal B. Chaudri, Awais Rashid, Roberto Zicari (Eds.): <ulink
                    url="http://www.aw.com/catalog/academic/product/1,4096,0201844524,00.html">XML
                    Data Management: Native XML and XML-Enabled Database Systems</ulink>. ISBN:
                0-201-84452-4. Published by Addison Wesley Professional, March, 2003.</para>

